<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 06 at 7:04PM MDT until July 06 at 10:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 745 PM MDT
FOR CENTRAL MEAGHER COUNTY...
At 703 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 35 miles northeast of Townsend to 6 miles east of
White Sulphur Springs, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
White Sulphur Springs, Fort Logan On The Smith River, Checkerboard,
Newlan Creek Reservoir and Fort Logan.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
